This workflow starts by importing bacterial abundance data and
metabolite concentration data into separate TreeSE data containers.
The TreeSE object is uniquely positioned to support optimized multi-assay
data access, manipulation, and visualization. The separate TreeSE objects
are linked together with MultiAssayExperiment (MAE) data container.
• Emerging analysis framework called miaverse (MIcrobiome Analysis uniVERSE)
utilizes a common, standardized data container, which enables highly optimized
integration of multi-assay microbiome profiling data from clinical studies.
• The miaverse contains methods for data analysis and visualization together
with comprehensive online documentation and tutorials.
• Common, shared data container enables usage of tools of other disciplines.
